        <mxCell id="FTPfOA1blvSSXFaizQHR-11" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;horizontal=1;fontSize=13;fontStyle=0" value="DataCore acts as a hub, forwarding machine data to all these systems. " vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="210" x="62.5" y="200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="FTPfOA1blvSSXFaizQHR-12" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;22ad4360d921&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The translator that reads raw STM32 data, decodes it using configuration from data cloud export, and publishes only the requested pieces via MQTT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="240" x="-370" y="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="FTPfOA1blvSSXFaizQHR-14" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:&#39;Segoe UI&#39;;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;line-height:20px&quot;&gt;Network Control is the central network manager for the Mk6 iMX9 system, and all other Mk6 applications talk to it through MQTT instead of talking directly to hardware.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="330" x="520" y="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="FTPfOA1blvSSXFaizQHR-19" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:&#39;Segoe UI&#39;;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;line-height:20px&quot;&gt;ac‑bookkeeper is a central MQTT service whose job is to coordinate MQTT topic requests and publishing flows between data users and data owners.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="310" x="450" y="340" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="FTPfOA1blvSSXFaizQHR-22" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(236, 236, 236); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;&quot;&gt;machine configuration data&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="200" x="-124.37" y="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="FTPfOA1blvSSXFaizQHR-23" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;22ad4360d921&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The translator that reads raw STM32 data, decodes it using configuration from data cloud export, and publishes only the requested pieces via MQTT.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Segoe UI&quot;&gt;DataCore acts as a hub, forwarding machine data to all these systems.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;; font-size: 14px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
